arm64: dts: h713: reboot-to-fastboot/bootloader handoff via RTC GP nvmem

Wire "reboot fastboot" and "reboot bootloader" from Linux to a fastboot
re-entry, respectively a U-Boot prompt, with no serial console attached, using
the RTC's general-purpose register 7 as the handoff word.

GP7 lives in the SoC's always-on RTC domain. A bench experiment wrote distinct
markers to all eight GP words, issued a warm reboot (PSCI SYSTEM_RESET -> BL31
-> watchdog), and read every marker back unchanged, so the register survives the
reset the kernel performs and the SPL does not clobber it. GP7 is the highest
word, furthest from the low GP words the vendor boot0 is known to touch.

The sun6i-rtc driver (now enabled, "allwinner,sun50i-h6-rtc") exposes the eight
GP words as a battery-backed nvmem device: SUN6I_GP_DATA is at register offset
0x100, so GP7 is nvmem byte offset 0x1c -> physical 0x0709011c. A fixed nvmem
cell child of the rtc node names that word; because devm_rtc_nvmem_register()
sets add_legacy_fixed_of_cells, the cell is registered against the rtc node's
of_node and is phandle-referenceable with no driver change.

nvmem-reboot-mode writes a per-mode magic to that cell: mode-fastboot
(0xfa57b007) on "reboot fastboot", mode-bootloader (0xb007c0de) on "reboot
bootloader"; a plain reboot writes nothing (the reboot-mode core skips a zero
magic). U-Boot's preboot reads GP7, clears it on a match, and either runs
fastboot or sets bootdelay -1 to fall through to its prompt. Clearing on consume
plus an indeterminate-but-typically-zero cold-boot value keeps a stale magic
from forcing an unexpected entry.

This replaces the previous single-mode syscon-reboot-mode window at 0x0709011c,
which overlapped the RTC register region the rtc driver now claims. Pairs with
CONFIG_RTC_DRV_SUN6I, CONFIG_RTC_NVMEM, and CONFIG_NVMEM_REBOOT_MODE in the bench
defconfig, and with a U-Boot preboot that dispatches on the two magics.

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-h713.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-h713.dtsi
@@ -30,6 +30,19 @@
 		stdout-path = "serial0:115200n8";
 	};
 
+	/* Reboot handoff via RTC GP7 (nvmem cell in &rtc; always-on domain,
+	 * survives the warm PSCI/watchdog reset). `reboot fastboot` writes the
+	 * fastboot magic and `reboot bootloader` the bootloader magic; U-Boot's
+	 * preboot reads GP7 and, per magic, enters fastboot or drops to its
+	 * prompt. Magics are unchanged on the U-Boot side. */
+	reboot-mode {
+		compatible = "nvmem-reboot-mode";
+		nvmem-cells = <&reboot_mode_magic>;
+		nvmem-cell-names = "reboot-mode";
+		mode-fastboot = <0xfa57b007>;
+		mode-bootloader = <0xb007c0de>;
+	};
+
 	aliases {
 		serial0 = &uart0;
 		mmc0 = &mmc2;
@@ -1169,6 +1182,15 @@
 			interrupts = <GIC_SPI 147 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
 			clock-output-names = "osc32k", "osc32k-out", "iosc";
 			#clock-cells = <1>;
+			#address-cells = <1>;
+			#size-cells = <1>;
+
+			/* GP7 (phys 0x0709011c) holds the reboot-mode magic handed to
+			 * U-Boot. The GP register block is nvmem offset 0, so GP7 is
+			 * byte offset 0x1c. */
+			reboot_mode_magic: reboot-mode-magic@1c {
+				reg = <0x1c 0x4>;
+			};
 		};
 
 		/*
